messages.content:
Perfect! Now I need to filter medals won when Ryan Held was in his twenties. He was born on June 27, 1995, so:
- He turned 20 on June 27, 2015
- He turned 30 on June 27, 2025

So his twenties span from June 27, 2015 to June 26, 2025. Looking at the medal years:
- 2016: He would be 20-21 (in his twenties)
- 2017: He would be 21-22 (in his twenties)
- 2018: He would be 22-23 (in his twenties)
- 2021: He would be 25-26 (in his twenties)
- 2022: He would be 26-27 (in his twenties)
- 2023: He would be 27-28 (in his twenties)

All the medals shown are in his twenties! Let me count them. Now let me write a proper SQL query to compute this answer.

function.arguments:
{"command": "cat <<'EOF' > /tmp/query.sql
SELECT COUNT(*) AS medal_count
FROM medal m
JOIN format f ON m.format_id = f.format_id
JOIN tournament t ON f.tournament_id = t.tournament_id
JOIN athlete a ON t.athlete_id = a.athlete_id
JOIN personalinformation p ON a.athlete_id = p.athlete_id
WHERE a.name = 'Ryan Held'
  AND m.year >= EXTRACT(YEAR FROM (TO_DATE(p.birth_year || '-' || p.birth_month || '-' || p.birth_day, 'YYYY-MM-DD') + INTERVAL '20 years'))
  AND m.year < EXTRACT(YEAR FROM (TO_DATE(p.birth_year || '-' || p.birth_month || '-' || p.birth_day, 'YYYY-MM-DD') + INTERVAL '30 years'));
EOF
cat /tmp/query.sql
"}
